# server4home deployment history — JSON event ledger.
#
# Each `server4home deploy` (and, when it lands, `apply` / `destroy`) writes a
# single JSON file here describing what happened: manifest path + git SHA,
# target, VM IP/vmid, installer versions, outcome (with failed_step on
# failures). The schema is documented in tools/server4home/history.py.
#
# These files are checked in to git — that's the durable record. Commit them
# alongside the manifest changes that triggered the deploy. After committing,
# regenerate the human-readable view:
#
#   just history          # rewrites docs/deployment-history.md
#
# This .gitkeep just ensures the directory exists in a fresh clone.
